{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce a Publicly Accessible Sex Offenders Register",
        "additional_details": "We urge the Government to legislate for a publicly accessible Sex Offenders Register as I believe the current \"Sarah\u2019s Law\" is reactive and insufficient; it requires parents to suspect a threat before acting. We believe that we need a proactive, searchable database that grants communities a \"right to know\" who lives among them, and that public safety and child protection must take priority over the privacy of convicted offenders. We think such a register could empower our neighbourhoods with transparency to prevent harm and enhance local safeguarding.",
        "background": "Introduce a public Sex Offenders Register. We believe \"Sarah\u2019s Law\" is too reactive, and that communities deserve a proactive \"right to know\". In our view, transparency must outrank offender privacy and we demand an official, searchable database to empower parents and enhance safety.",
